      "body": "While going through the Testing Guide's [v3 transaction section](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/bitcoin-devwiki/wiki/27.0-Release-Candidate-Testing-Guide#v3-transaction-policy) I noticed that if one attempts to do a `testmempoolaccept` just before the last `submitpackage`, the former would reject the input, but the latter would still allow it.\r\n```console\r\n$ bcli testmempoolaccept \"[\\\"$v3_parent_signed_tx\\\",\\\"$high_fee_child_signed_tx\\\"]\"\r\n[\r\n  {\r\n    \"txid\": \"e40a9567347a3eace38f6e8c05d437c1c56460ad34ddeed724e595f776e16bff\",\r\n    \"wtxid\": \"06551611e1c23087abd4f72d928c55ec69cf30cb19f5ffa7af00a87b8d77ad40\",\r\n    \"allowed\": false,\r\n    \"reject-reason\": \"txn-already-in-mempool\"\r\n  },\r\n  {\r\n    \"txid\": \"66c8a8dfa2ba6995caae3dd1f109ea37408dd65f0a94cc2cd0872a4a5604a2a9\",\r\n    \"wtxid\": \"0a67d798ad3f8be6875dfaa562cc1f2dd15b70e368c915cdca0e66e2a686c952\"\r\n  }\r\n]\r\n```",
